# Data cleaning: Handle missing values
data["Gross"] = data["Gross"].str.replace("$", "").str.replace("M", "").str.replace(",", "")
data["Gross"] = pd.to_numeric(data["Gross"], errors="coerce")
data.fillna({"Gross": data["Gross"].mean()}, inplace=True)

In [13]:
# Visualization 4: Elbow Method for Optimal K in K-Means Clustering
k_values = range(1, 11)
inertias = []
for k in k_values:
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=0)
    kmeans.fit(data[["IMDB Rating", "Gross"]])
    inertias.append(kmeans.inertia_)

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.plot(k_values, inertias, marker="o")
plt.title("Elbow Method for Optimal K")
plt.xlabel("Number of Clusters (K)")
plt.ylabel("Inertia")
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()
In [14]:
# K-Means Clustering with optimal K (e.g., K=3)
kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=3, random_state=0)
data["Cluster"] = kmeans.fit_predict(data[["IMDB Rating", "Gross"]])

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.scatterplot(x=data["IMDB Rating"], y=data["Gross"], hue=data["Cluster"], palette="viridis", s=100)
plt.title("K-Means Clustering (K=3)")
plt.xlabel("IMDB Rating")
plt.ylabel("Gross (in millions)")
plt.legend(title="Cluster")
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()
In [15]:
# Line fitting: Linear Regression - IMDB Rating vs Gross
X = data["IMDB Rating"].values.reshape(-1, 1)
y = data["Gross"].values

X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=0)

model = LinearRegression()
model.fit(X_train, y_train)

# Predictions
y_pred = model.predict(X_test)

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.scatter(X, y, alpha=0.6, label="Data", edgecolor='k')
plt.plot(X, model.predict(X), color="red", label="Best Fit Line")
plt.title("Linear Regression: IMDB Rating vs Gross")
plt.xlabel("IMDB Rating")
plt.ylabel("Gross (in millions)")
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()
